    "common_miss_reason": "Weak-side shooters hold their spot waiting for the kickout. The stunt only buys a half-second window — if the shooter doesn't widen, the defender recovers before the pass can arrive clean.",
    "why_best_read_works": "The stunt commits the defender's hips and weight to the ball. A drift wider on the arc moves the catch point further from his recovery path — the pass arrives clean and the closeout is too long to contest the shot.",
    "decoder_teaching_point": "When your defender stunts at the ball, slide wider on the arc. The kickout lane opens, and his closeout has to cover a longer distance.",
    "lesson_connection": "empty-space-cut",
    "explanation_md": "**Same stunt, almost no hints.** The arrow and the cone are both off — all you have left is the help pulse and what his body tells you. Watch his feet and his weight. The instant they shift to the ball, he has committed, and you are open. Slide wider the moment you feel it. This is how the read looks in a real game: nobody marks the help for you, so you learn to feel it.",
